 simmering basket (pears should sit comfortably in basket and not obstruct hole in mixing bowl lid. If pears are crowded, place 2 of the pears into Varoma dish). Set aside."},{"content":"Place water, cinnamon, ginger, vanilla bean seeds and pod, honey and salt into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket (place Varoma into position, if required) and cook <b>20-25 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>, until pears are softened but still holding their shape.  Check to see if pears are cooked; if still firm cook for a further <b>5-10 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer pears into a large bowl."},{"content":"To thicken syrup, cook <b>20 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid."},{"content":"Strain syrup through a fine mesh sieve over pears, then allow pears and syrup to cool completely, turning pears regularly in the syrup as they cool (approx. 30 minutes). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Chocolate sauce"},{"content":"Place chocolate into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add remaining sauce ingredients and heat <b>1 min 30 sec - 2 min\/50°C\/speed 3<b>, or until melted. Transfer into a small bowl."},{"content":"Carefully dip cooled pears in chocolate sauce and place into refrigerator to set (approx. 5 minutes). Serve pears with nut crumble and garnish with mint leaves."}],"hintsAndTricks":["It is important that the pears do not obstruct the hole in the mixing bowl lid. If the pears are crowded, it will take longer for them to cook.","To save time, start on step 4 while the nut crumble is in the oven. You can also drizzle the pears with chocolate just before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 10m","4 portions"]}